name: src/index.js
ESDocUploader
description:
ESDocUploader, connects with the [ESDoc hosting service](https://doc.esdoc.org/) and tell it
to generage the documentation for your project.

name: constructor
description: Create a new instance of the uploader.

params.name: url
params.description:
This is the GitHub repository url. You can also ignore it and
                              it will automatically search for it on your `package.json`.

name: _messages
description: A list of pre defined messages that the class will log.

name: url
description:
The repository url. It can be null if the one provided is not valid or if there isn't
one on the `package.json`.

name: _uploading
description: A flag to know if the class it's currently uploading something.

name: _api
description:
A small dictionary used to store information relative to the ESDoc API, like it's
main domain or the path to create a new doc.

name: _finishFile
description: The name of the file where the class it's going to check if the docs were uploaded.

name: _intervalTime
description:
The amount of time the class will wait between checks to see if the docs site was
generated.

name: _path
description:
After the first request, this is where the returned path for the docs on the server
will be stored.

name: _callback
description: A callback that will be executed after confirmation that the docs were generated.

name: _indicatorText
description: The text that will show up on the terminal.

name: _indicatorInterval
description: The amout of time in which the indicator will be updated.

name: _indicatorCounter
description: A utility counter to know how many dos will be added to the indicator

name: _indicatorLimit
description:
After this many iterations, the dots will start to be removed instead of added. When the
counter hits 0, it will start adding again, until it hits this limit.

name: _indicatorIncrease
description: A flag to know if the indicator it's currently adding dots or removing them.

name: canUpload
description:
After the class is istantiated, this method can be used to check if the url is valid and
if the method `upload` can be called

name: upload
description: Upload your documentation to the ESDoc API.

params.name: callback
params.description:
=> {}] - An optional callback to be executed after
everthing is ready.

name: _retrieveUrlFromPackage
description: Tries to retrieve the repository url from your `pacakge.json`.

return.description: The repository url that was on your `package.json`.

name: _buildUrl
description: Generates a new url with the required format to use with the ESDoc API.

return.description: The new url, on the required format for ESDoc.

name: _validateUrl
description: Validates a given url to see if it has the required format by the ESDoc API.

return.description:
If the url it's valid, it will return it, otherwise, itw will
return null.

name: _startAsking
description:
This method is called after the initial request to the API, and tells the class to check
every X seconds to see if the documentation was uploaded.

name: _ask
description: It makes a request to check if the documentation was uploaded or not.

name: _finish
description:
This method is called after it's confirmed that the documentation was successfully uploaded,
and it stops teh indicator, logs a mesage with the url for the documetation and invokes the
callback set in the `upload()` method.

name: _getAPIUrl
description: Returns a url for the ESDoc API.

params.name: type
params.description:
The type of url you need. This is parameter it's the key for the
                        `_api` dictionary.

return.description:
It will return the API domain and the value in the `_api` dictionary for
                 given type.

name: _setAPIUrl
description:
Set a new type of urlf or the ESDoc API. For example, the first request will return a
relative path for the documentation, this class will use this method to save this path
so it can be later be retrieved using `_getAPIUrl` and it wil already have the API main
domain.

params.name: url
params.description: The relative url you want to save.

name: _logError
description: Logs an eror message to the terminal.

params.name: error
params.description:
This can be the message you want to log, a key for the
                              `_messages` dictionary or an `Error` object.

name: _startIndicator
description: Starts showing the progress indicator on the terminal.

name: _runIndicator
description: The actual method that shows the progress indicator on the terminal.

name: _stopIndicator
description: Removes the progress indicator from the terminal.

name: _restartLine
description:
Removes everything on the current terminal line and sets the cursor to the initial
position.

name: _print
description: Writes a message in the terminal.
